            <title>[JCR-1222] Index nodes in parallel</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-1222</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>CPUs with multiple cores are now standard and Jackrabbit should make use of it where it makes sense. Analyzing content while a node is indexed is quite costly, but can be broken easily into task that can be executed in parallel. E.g. index multiple nodes in parallel.</description>
